The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Shimla, April 22 (PTI): The Himachal Pradesh government today banned littering of public places and the use of polythene bags.          
	A Rs 50 fine will be imposed for littering, the forest and environment minister said while launching an anti-pollution drive on World Earth Day. Members of a patrol will blow their whistles if they find anyone littering.                   
	Guruvayoor (PTI): A devotee weighed himself against 72kg of paracetamol tablets while offering thulabaram at the Sri Krishna temple in Kerala. Thulabaram is an act of weighing oneself against commodities. Satyan performed the ritual for his father, a medicine wholesaler. Temple authorities later donated the pills to the government hospital here.                   
	New Delhi: A 12-year-old girl died after a suspected cardiac arrest while jogging a lap of her school ground on Tuesday, but neither the girls parents nor police are revealing whether she had a history of heart ailment. Surabhi Rajput, a student of Class VII, was completing a warm up lap before a game of football when she collapsed, an official at the Noida school said.                   
	Vadodara (PTI): Pakistan has arrested 18 Indian fishermen from the Arabian Sea off the coast of Kutch. Gujarat agriculture and fisheries minister Dilip Sanghani will take up the issue of their release with the Centre.                  
	Ahmednagar (PTI): A district consumer forum in Maharashtra has ordered an ophthalmologist couple to pay Rs 1 lakh in compensation and Rs 25,000 as litigation charges to a patient who suffered permanent eye damage after being operated on by the couple.                   
	 Rajkot (PTI): Mustaq Rahimtullah Miyana, 36, a convict in Morbi jail, attempted suicide by hitting his head against the iron bar of a cupboard on Monday, police said. He sustained severe head injuries and was taken to hospital. Miyana, whose transfer application had been rejected, alleged that he was severely beaten up by a guard when caught supplying gutkha to prisoners.                                                                                                                         
